To Vietson<br>
At the time of the assissination Kennedy was as surprised about the killing as were the Vietnamese people. Had he ordered Diem's assassination via the CIAor that he had knowledge of such a deed by the CIA  is very questionable. <br>
Many believed Diem's murder was a means toward ending the war sooner. What is surprising that no formal investigation was ever conducted into his killing by either the US government nor the South Vietnames government. <br><br>
While I don't agree with some of the things the PBS television series presented on the Vietnam war, there were some interesting notes on Diem's government if I remember correctly and the book, &quot;Vietnam: A History, a companion to the PBS Television Series on Vietnam might give you some insights, the author is Stanley Karnow.  Another interesting book is &quot;Vietnam at War, The History 1946-1975, by Phillip B. Davidson,Oxford Press 1987.&quot;<br>
The north took advantage of the disarray that followed and moved in more troops into the south and the VC  used the incident to stir up catholics against the US government. It's no secret that Kennedy and others wanted Diem to be replaced and looked for a replacement. I know we didn't want him coming to the US and I believe he had made arrangements to leave South Vietnam. The US was pleased with that arrangement, but I believe it was Diem's own arrogance and desire to be recognized as an individual  of importance deserving special arrangements and recognition that directly contributed toward his assiassionation by his own former generals and supporters. <br><br>
Vietson,may you finds what you are looking for, I've found it best to look at what everyone else has said about an individual, and ask why the writer or spokesmen said what he did. Often that gives you a lot of answers, and information from which you can form your own opinion. the individuals responsible for Diem's assassination had very good reasons to blame the US governemnt for their own misdeeds.  <br><br>
sorry about the misspelled words. <br>
but i'm sure john or tom will correct them for me.<br><br>

